  - For each task/partition, a separate Python worker process is spawned (not a thread)\
  - These are separate OS processes, each with their own Python interpreter and GIL\
  - So they CAN run truly in parallel (no GIL contention between workers)\
  - The JVM runs the task scheduler as threads\
  - Each Python worker is a separate `python` process\
