  - In local mode, the driver IS the executor, and tasks run as threads in the JVM, but each task spawns a separate Python worker subprocess that executes the actual Python code in parallel \
  across multiple processes.\
  - This means Python UDFs bypass the GIL and run truly concurrently, while the JVM coordinates everything with a single executor that has N slots corresponding to available cores.\
